FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG INVESTMENT took command from the start, was nudged along unchallenged throughout the turn, was finally roused in mid stretch and kept on to hold safe at the wire. TRICKY MAGICIAN was unhurried near the back in the early stages, made a good move on the rail at the three eighths marker, loomed the threat in the two path turning for home but could not reel in the front running winner who had something in reserve. MAXIMUS MOMENTUS broke in a tangle at the start to trail in the beginning, advanced on the rail picking up foes on the turn, slipped up the fence in upper stretch to contend, angled outside to the three path at the furlong pole and finished up to be a non threaten clear third in the end. SEA SCOUT broke inwards at the start, regrouped to track the pacesetter between with four furlongs remaining, could not match strides with rivals losing ground to the leaders on the turn and re-rallied on the fence the final sixteenth to capture a minor share. STORMY SOUL broke in the air to begin, recovered to chase the frontrunner down the backstretch, was ridden three wide to keep position but to no avail two furlongs from home and retreated between horses through the stretch. WENJACK had a good spot three deep watching the top pair down the backside, offered a brief run outside foes with three furlongs to go making little gain on the leaders by the quarter marker and levelled out in the five path in the last eighth. RACING IN THE RAIN was allowed to settle just off the rail at the half near the back, could not get involved seeing the field on the turn and found little on the fence down the lane to be a factor.

SING DIXIE was taken a hold of while in tight between foes soon after the break, settled near the rear outside three deep down the backside, rallied three wide circling runners commencing at the three furlong marker, closed in on the lead at the eighth pole but could not match strides with the late surging winner in the final sixteenth and settled for second best on this day. IT'S ME MARIO was hustled to try to get the lead outside after the start, chased the pace three deep at the half, hounded the frontrunner throughout the turn and faded in mid stretch. J M R TUREK broke in brushing inside rival at the start, had a good spot watching the top four battle in early backstretch, advanced between horses midpoint on the turn and was one paced through the stretch. UNEXPECTED OUTCOME (IRE) pressed the issue three wide at the start, was reined back off the early speed duel with eleven sixteenths to go, was steadied between runners at the three furlong marker and was not persevered with at the quarter pole to the wire. MY SONG BABY was part of the early four pronged speed duel early on, prompted the pace in between foes two wide at the half, gave way with runners on either side at the three furlong marker and stopped at the quarter pole.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 3 6F All Weather Track CR: 85. Maiden Special Weight Purse 111600. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR REDEMPTION took control throughout the back straight, was headed outside at the two furlong pole,, dueled stubbornly inside turning for home and began to edge away in the final sixteenth in a gritty performance up front throughout. ROYAL QUALITY prompted outside down the backstretch, applied more pressure outside to be head and head with the winner at the quarter pole, fought on determinedly in upper stretch, could not find more at the furlong marker and had to settle for second best at the finish. TOWN'S WARRIOR tracked the frontrunner on the rail down the backside, was roused to go after the contesting top pair midway on the turn, swung out three deep for the drive to the wire, shifted back inwards to the rail at the eighth pole and was gaining slowly to finish up a non threatening third in the end. KID MARVELOUS settled in midpack alone at the half, was roused with five sixteenths to go with rivals on either side, continued to keep pace with others to be in the hunt in lane five at the top of the stretch and finished up evenly to the wire holding for a minor share in the end. ALPHA MEISTER dwelt at the start spotting the field to begin, recovered by the half to be in contention with the pack inside, rallied three wide between runners three furlongs to home, was in range six wide outside horses at the top of the stretch but could not sustain his run trying to overcome the poor start and stalled in the final sixteenth. THE NEW MAYBE was allowed to settle near the back outside down the backstretch, could not keep pace with others four wide outside horses with three furlongs remaining, could see the field in the four path straightening out for the drive, shifted in to the rail at the furlong marker but could not make any impression inside to the finish. SPEEDY N SMART was away slowly on the break, was shuffled back when in tight quarters on the rail entering the turn to trail the field and could not make any impact running on the fence to the wire.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUNRISE DRIVE was caught five wide into the first turn racing toward the back, eased back off trailing rivals and tucked in a bit thereupon racing just a few paths off the rail, trailed up the backstretch and was ridden along coming to the half, swung eight deep turning for home, kicked on with a sustained rally to get the lead seventy yards out and edge clear. SOLAR moved forward under mild early encouragement, pressed from outside just off the leader three to four deep, bid past the three-eighths drawing even, contended for the lead while drifting five wide into upper stretch, continued to dog it out bumping a rival in the process, was no match for the winner but got the place. RELIABILITY was coaxed forward but caught four to five wide into and on the first turn, stalked the leading pair from outside up the backstretch, continued wide on the far turn floating six deep turning for home, bid at the furlong pole putting a nose in front, was bumped by a rival late and outkicked. DIXIE GIANT got away alertly and went straight to the fore to set the terms racing well off the rail in the three path into the turn, continued up the backstretch off the inside with outside pressure, was challenged into the far turn, drifted out a bit in the stretch but fought on. H C HOLIDAY stalked from mid-pack between runners initially going two to three wide on the first turn, moved out a bit on the far turn and into the stretch, ran on evenly. JACK THE CAT tracked from inside just off and in behind the leaders, came out a bit at the top of the stretch then altered back in to the two path at the furlong marker with plenty of room if good enough but could only go on evenly late. DESOLATOR settled at the rear shifting in, advanced a position up the backstretch, saved ground on the far turn, needed more. NATIVE PRINCE raced outside foes three to four wide mid-division through the first turn, came out six wide turning for home, was never far off the lead but unable to threaten.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUIET OUT EAST was content loping along on a long rein sitting outside the flank of the leader in the beginning, was even with the pacesetter outside at the three eighths pole, poked his head in front five wide outside straightening out for the drive at the quarter pole, surrendered the lead briefly drifting out under left handed urged with three sixteenths to go, took back the lead at the furlong marker and held off the new challenger at the wire. KIDDIE HOLIDAY had a good spot tracking the top duo outside in the beginning, started to reel in the embattled pair with five sixteenths from the wire, continued to close the gap with each stride at the top of the lane, loomed the threat in the final sixteenth inside and just missed the nod at the wire in the win photo. JUST START ME UP pulled the rider to the lead setting a soft pace in the early going, was headed outside by the winner three furlongs from the wire, gave way momentarily at the quarter pole, resurged inside to poke his nose in front with three sixteenths to go, stubbornly battled from the eighth pole to the wire but gave way grudgingly late and had to settle for third in a hard fought effort. CANADIAN PHAROAH tracked in the second flight on the rail down the backside, was asked for more run on the rail midway through the turn, had no response, trailed in the two path straightening out for the drive and showed some late interest to pass tired runners in the final eighth. LION KINGDOM was unhurried on the rail near the back, offered a mild turn of foot to battle between foes at the three eighths marker, fought on in upper stretch but yielded in the last sixteenth losing a placing late. SAND DANCER took some awkward steps leaving the gate, losing action to be well behind the pack trailing down the backstretch, was roused entering the turn catching up to the field four wide around horses with three furlongs remaining, was in with a chance outside for a share of the prize turning for home passing some runners but could not sustain the run and tired in mid stretch.

DANCIN' DEPUTY had a good position tracking the top pair outside at the half mile marker, close in on the leaders when asked midpoint on the turn to battle three deep straightening out for the drive, continued to dig in fighting for the front at the sixteenth pole but needed a little more late and gave way in deep stretch holding on to the show award in the end in a gutsy effort. PALACE RING had a slim lead down the back straight, continued to keep his head in front while hounded outside through the turn, was clinging onto the lead when collared by three rivals outside at the top of the stretch, kept on going until the sixteenth pole and finally gave way late holding for a minor share in a determined front running attempt.
